      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_GetTableNameAndRowCount",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to populate a table named "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Utils.TableNameAndRowCount",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " with the schema name, table name, and row count for each table in the current database. It iterates over all tables, retrieves the row count for each, and inserts this information into the specified table."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves several steps, including cursor operations, dynamic SQL execution, and data insertion. While the logic is straightforward, the use of cursors and dynamic SQL adds a layer of complexity that requires careful handling to ensure performance and security."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "This stored procedure does not take any input parameters. It operates on the current database context and retrieves information about all tables within it."
        }
      ]
    },
